Name: Performed task: Flatworm exit
ContentData:
* ran full canister of carbon
* 20g water change
started at 11:30a and watched all day. took about 3 minutes before planaria started to die. started carbon when they started dying. had a planaria snow storm for a while until they were filtered out or dissolved. there still appears to be some planaria left but they are not moving much. they are probably dead or dying.
corals appear to be stressed, which is to be expected. they do not look any worse than other times of significant planaria removal via siphon.

Name: heater working well now
ContentData:
Since using the BRS heat controller, the heater is working well. The original port is the heater was plugged in is not now working properly and controls the heat controller.
Star no longer controls the heater but still is in place for overheat and for water changes.

Name: updated code on controller
